import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('S&P 500 Index')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the S&P 500 index prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Price")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    monthly_returns = data.groupby('month')['price'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(monthly_returns.index, monthly_returns.values, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=monthly_returns.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Monthly Return')
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Monthly Return')
    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(1, 13))
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'])
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sp500 = data['price']
    other_indices = ['dow_jones', 'nasdaq', 'nikkei', 'hang_seng']
    for index in other_indices:
        plt.scatter(data['date'], data[index], label=index)
    plt.plot(data['date'], sp500, color='black', label='S&P 500')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the S&P 500 index and other major stock indices?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'], color='blue', label='S&P 500 Index Prices')
    ax.fill_between(data['date'], data['price'] - data['price'].std(), data['price'] + data['price'].std(), alpha=0.2, color='blue', label='Standard Deviation')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
